definition.value: A biladiene that is the 15-oxo derivative of beta-bilirubin.

An Ins-1-P-Cer-C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 40 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-Cer-C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-Cer-C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-Cer-C(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 46 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.

An Ins-1-P-Cer D(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 42 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and one other unspecified position, and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-vinylbacteriochlorophyll a.

An Ins-1-P-Cer D(1-) in which the acyl group and the ceramide base contain a total of 44 carbons and 0 double bonds, with the acyl group hydroxylated at position 2 and one other unspecified position, and the ceramide base hydroxylated at position 4.
A member of the class of isoflavones having one or more glycosyl residues attached at unspecified positions.
An organic phosphorothioate anion that is the conjugate base of cysteamine S-phosphate, obtained by deprotonation of the two free thiophosohate OH groups and protonation of the amino group.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a pyran ring fused on to a chromane skeleton.
A member of the class of  cardenolides that is 7,8-epoxycard-20(22)-enolide substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 14 (the 3beta,5beta,7beta stereoisomer).
Any steroid lactone that is a  C23 steroid with a five-membered lactone ring at C-17 and its substituted derivatives. They form the aglycone constituents of cardiac glycosides.

An N(4)-glycosylated L-asparagine residue in which the glycosyl element is a branched undecasaccharide comprising a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl chain, to the mannosyl residue of which are linked (1->3) and (1->6) two alpha-sialyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl units.
A nucleotide residue derived from N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A nucleotide-amino acid that is the N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyl derivative of adenine 5'-monophosphate.
A nucleotide residue derived from N(6)-dimethylallyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A  N-acetyl-L-amino acid that is the N-acetyl derivative of L-tryptophan.
A nucleotide residue derived from 2-thio-N(6)-dimethylallyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is AMP substituted at C-2 by a thio group and at N-6 by a dimethylallyl group.
Any organic aromatic compound with a structure based on a phenethyl alcohol skeleton and its substituted derivatives.
A nucleotide residue derived from 2-methylthio-N(6)-dimethylallyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is AMP substituted at C-2 by a methylthio group and at N-6 by a dimethylallyl group.
A nucleotide residue derived from 2-thio-N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A nucleotide-amino acid that is the N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyl derivative of 2-thioadenine 5'-monophosphate.

An  organic heteropentacyclic compound that is naloxone substituted in which the allyl group attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a cyclopropylmethyl group. A mu-opioid receptor antagonist, it is used to treat alcohol dependence.
A nucleotide residue derived from 2-methylthio-N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3'- and 5'-positions.
A nucleotide-amino acid that is the N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyl derivative of 2-methylthioadenine 5'-monophosphate.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from 3-thio-L-aspartic acid
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is L-aspartic acid substituted at position 3 by a thio (sulfanyl) group.

An organic heterohexacyclic compound and spirooxindole-type pyranopyrimidine spiro compound in which the shared atom of the spiro system is the carbon at position 3 of 1-allyl-7-fluoro-1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one.
An organic cationic group derived from 7-methylguanosine 5'-triphosphate.
An optically active form of O(4)-phosphonatotyrosine(2-) having D-configuration.
An organic cationic group derived from N(2),N(2),N(7)-trimethylguanosine 5'-triphosphate.
A guanosine 5'-phosphate that is the N(2),N(2),N(7)-trimethyl derivative of guanosine 5'-triphosphate.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is estr-4-en-3-one substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 17.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoic acid.
An imidazolidinone that is imidazolidine which is substituted by oxo groups at positions 2, 4 and 5.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosatetraenoic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z)-3-oxohexacosapentaenoyl-CoA.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-tetracosatetraenoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (10Z,13Z,16Z)-3-oxodocosatrienoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-oxotetracosatetraenoic acid.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:1 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A guanosine 5'-phosphate that is the N(2),N(2),N(7)-trimethyl derivative of guanosine 5'-monophosphate.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both oleoyl.
A  phosphatidylcholine 36:3 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 38:5 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A nucleotide residue derived from 5,6-dihydrouridine 5'-monophosphate.
